ENTRY            A0156   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0156001   20260126   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 14         38
TITLE      Further measurement of the 7Be(p,gamma)8B cross section
           at low energies with the coulomb dissociation of 8B
AUTHOR     (T.Kikuchi, T.Motobayashi, N.Iwasa, Y.Ando, M.Kurokawa,
           S.Moriya, H.Murokami, T.Nishio, J.Ruan, S.Shirato,
           S.Shimura, T.Uchibori, Y.Yanagisawa, T.Kubo, H.Sakurai,
           T.Teranishi, Y.Watanabe, M.Ishihara, M.Hirai,
           T.Nakamara, S.Kubono, M.Gai, R.H.France IIi, K.H.Hahn,
           Th.Delbar, P.Lipnik, C.Michotte)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,3,213,1998)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNYOK,2JPNIPC,2JPNTOK,1USAUCO,1USAYAL,2BLGLVN)
FACILITY   (ISOCY,2JPNIPC) radioactive beam line
METHOD     (EXTB,SITA,EDE)
           The dE-E system detected the reaction products, proton
           and 7Be, in coincidence, and the NaI(Tl) was used for
           measuring the gamma-rays from the first excited state
           of 7Be at 429 keV.
INC-SOURCE Secondary 8B beams of 2x10**4/s bombarded a 50 mg/cm2
           208Pb target.
DETECTOR   (NAICR,SCIN) E-dE plastic detector hodoscope.
           The detection efficiency is evaluated by Monte-Carlo
           simulation.
           The detection system consisted of a dE-E plastic
           scintillator hodoscope and a NaI(Tl) detector
           array DALI (see REL-REF).
REL-REF    (I,,T.Nishio+,P,A-JCL-29,1996) detector array DALI
ADD-RES    S-factor at zero energy is deduced.
CORRECTION In order to deduce absolute cross sections, corrections
           are made for the loss of fragment due to the reactions
           in the detector material (7% of the total yield), the
           dissociation reaction feeding the 429 keV state of 7-Be
            (5% on an average), and the pile-up rejection (2%).
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) An overall systematic uncertainty in
           corrections
STATUS     (UNOBT) 20-Apr-2001 the letter has been sent to
           T.Motobayashi. A reply is absent.
HISTORY    (20010526C)
           (20090921A) BIB section updated
           (20260126A) SD: Corrections in both Subents.
ENDBIB              38
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
      2.
ENDCOMMON            3
